      "lesson title": "AI in Humanitarian Aid Distribution",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "In humanitarian crises, aid organisations increasingly rely on artificial intelligence to help decide who receives support, when, and in what quantities. However, when the data feeding these systems is incomplete, biased, or poorly collected, the consequences can be severe, leaving vulnerable people without the help they urgently need. This lesson introduces beginners to the ways in which flawed data can distort AI-driven aid distribution, resulting in unequal or delayed support for affected communities. You will explore real-world examples that illustrate how data quality directly shapes the decisions these systems make, and why understanding this link is essential for anyone working in or alongside the humanitarian sector. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer picture of the risks involved and the practical steps organisations can take to improve the reliability of their data before it reaches an AI system.",
